@kennknowles I'm basically talking about something like this: https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/9ed98f2e5a32fb14de03b9a8ea1dd45851cc3a7e/flink-tests/src/test/java/org/apache/flink/test/checkpointing/utils/StatefulJobSavepointFrom12MigrationITCase.java#L153-L153

Each operator does one verification and updates a unique accumulator. The `restoreAndExecute()` listens on the accumulators and waits until each one of them is reported.

In Beam, the operators that update the Accumulator (or Metric) would be `PAssert` operators that each have a unique ID for their assert. The `TestPipeline` would then listen on the IDs that it can get using pipeline traversal.
